https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/w500null The January 12th, 2010 earthquake in Haiti was one of the deadliest earthquakes ever recorded in history. Overnight Haiti lost 80% of its gross national product. Narrated by Mario L. Delatour, "35 long seconds: Haiti’s deadly earthquake" records the sad events on that ill fated day. 35 Long Seconds: Haiti’s Deadly Earthquake
